descript.abstract: This dataset is preliminary and was developed by combining the 2010 city boundaries for the cities of: Jurapa Valley and Eastvale, with the 2009 boundaries for the rest of the cities in the SCAG region. The dataset is comprised of data collected from each of the 6 counties contained within the SCAG region. The data represents the city boundary for each of the 191 cities in the region. Data was obtained from county representatives between April and May 2009 to reflect the most current updates and annexations to the city boundaries. The original data sources were the local LAFCO offices

procstep.procdesc: Data compiled from various sources (LAFCO county officies) and were re-projected. The city boundaries for Imperial County and San Bernardino were updated on 10/28/2009 and custom projected to incorporate the latest changes.

Sliver polygons were eliminated and city boundaries were adjusted along county boundaries to ensure geographic (positional) accuracy. The performed boundary adjustments were minimal and do not modify significantly the actual shape or position of the city limit.

City boundaries were compiled to a single geodatabase file. The table of attributes was updated to include: feature area, perimeter, city_id (census FIPS -place id ), acreage, and x,y coordinates of polygon centroids.
